Consider the following sets: 

A = {1, 2} 

B = {2, 3} 

C = {3, 4} 

Find the Cartesian products of A and (B ∩ C) and (A × B) ∩ (A × C). Show that these two sets are not equal and therefore, prove that the Cartesian product of two sets is not associative with respect to intersection.

